description: ...with the original drawing used for the cover!
name: Dolce luna
Jack lo svelto e Frank il lento
Gianni Rossi boscaiolo specializzato praticamente nudista

description: The Avengers travel to the Dark Avengers’ home dimension! Without knowing their domain’s laws of physics, however, the Avengers have a tough fight ahead of them!
...with the original drawing used for the cover!
name: Nel paradiso terrestre

description: After Valerie and Barry wreck Wally's first date with Crystal with their mad ninja skills, Wally finds out that taking his date home will probably be a fight, too!

The Bronze Age

The Super Wizard's quest to build an army of himself from across continuity continues--this time into the Bronze Age. He discovers social justice, swords of sorcery and a hint of the super-mega-crossover event comics that have conquered his world. Can these disparate versions of the Super Wizard help? Or is the world doomed in the coming Dark Age...?
name: The Bronze Age

description:
Mythic critters, flashbacks and answers to those longing questions? That can only mean one thing... The Crew is Back in this, the third collection of Biff the Vampire!

Volume Three collects the story strips one hundred and nine through one hundred fifty-seven, spanning the bulk of 2010 with a special spotlight on Biff's catgirl roommate Vida de Santos. Also included are rarely seen pencil strips and as-yet-unseen images of Vida. All this in a handy dandy PDF!

Contents: Story Strips No. 109 through 157. Also included are rarely seen Black & White and Full Color images plus a character spotlight on Vida and her creation.
name: La Gata

description: After a mysteries monster trashes his school, Jason leaps into action. Having never practiced with his powers before he easily bested. Jason’s friend Tim noticed how much Jason “sucked” and organised a training session, however Jason loses his cool while practicing.

Sister Long and her companion try everything to find new people to teach, and their efforts are finally paying off. Sister Long feels more and more of the joy that comes from helping the Japanese people deepen their relationship with God.
name: Month 8: September

volume.name: DENDO: One Year and One Half in Tokyo

description:
Meat/Soup Macaroni and Yak Hotdish

After sleeping half the day away... Bob finally wakes up. He realizes that it is indeed Tuesday and he told his parents he would visit them on Tuesday. Dread sets in. After a long and boring bus ride.. Bob finally makes it to his parent's house. During supper.. Bob's Meat/Soup Macaroni and Yak Hotdish stands up and lectures him on the finer points of exoplanets orbiting other stars.
name: Meat/Soup Macaroni and Yak Hotdish

description:
How Would I Know if You're Dreaming? is the third volume of Finn and Charlie Are Hitched, and contains comics run online in 2010 and 2011. It includes such storylines as Charlie's Indie Rock Beard, Finn's Dream, Candy's Long-Lost Daughter, and When Finn Met Charlie.

Finn and Charlie Are Hitched is a slice-of-life comic about a gay couple and their friends. It was nominated for an Ignatz award in 2011 in two categories: Outstanding Online Comic and Promising New Talent.
name: How Would I Know if You're Dreaming?

description:
"Son of Frankenbeans" - Doctor Frankenbeans is on the verge of his greatest creation ever. Success is within his grasp' so what could possibly go wrong?

"The Ribcage Halloween Special" - It's that time of year again. A time for tricks and a time for treats. But in a town full of ghouls, ghosts and assorted monsters, what exactly is Halloween like? Sara Morningstar is wondering just that.
name: Son of Frankenbeans; The Ribcage Halloween Special

description:
Deadly Silence Part 2

The Silence has struck! Now the Guardians must figure out a way to stop the assassin before its too late! The conclusion of "Deadly Silence" has come!
name: Deadly Silence Part 2

description: The Conclusion of Judges the miniseries is finally here. Will Ehud's parents be rescued from Jinn? Will all the Judges survive? Is there a traitor in the group? All will be answered in the exciting conclusion to Judges.

Part II

After rescuing Rose from the clutches of the evil Mayor, the Sheriff and his new companion set off at full speed to try to escape the grasp of the Coalition before the full scale of the massacre at Whitechapel is known.
name: Part II

description: Prison officials are baffled about the spate of murders in their penitentiary. But they may have bigger problems on their hands. As we find out in this issue, everybody has something to hide.

Squiggle's Revolt

The reader is introduced to Squiggle as she stages a jailbreak of Electrolyte and Pell Mell. But ThinkTank joins forces with Conniption and Honey Badger to lure Electrolyte back in his web.
name: Squiggle's Revolt

volume.name: The Misadventures of Electrolyte and The Justice Purveyors

description:
'Murica

The Matador crosses the border into America. What he finds is possibly more deadly than any monster he has ever faced. Can he survive the experience?
name: 'Murica

description:
The Fallen

This is a reboot of Issue 1 with a new artist. A woman takes her child and runs from the monster that has held her captive.
name: The Fallen

description: After the events of the Anathema War, only one of the O Men members is left – Vixen – and she decides to pick up the pieces and form a new O Men team. But how will she cope when things don’t go smoothly? Featuring the first appearances of Diva, Glitter and Liberty, plus a special anthology issues featuring top self-publishing talent! Collects The O Men issues 2.1 to 2.7.
name: Book Four

volume.name: The O Men: The Complete Story

description:
Based on Rikki-Tikki-Tavi from Rudyard Kipling's The Jungle Book.

As Rikki's new friends Darzee and Khan help him try to regain his memory, Nag and Nagaina dispatch the dusty brown snakeling Karait to do away with the mongoose before his memories return.

A vicious alien villain, greatest nemesis of the Cosmic Guardians, has been defeated for good. The Shaman's mission? Bring her back. But those space-faring heroes aren't too happy to hear about her return. Now former superhero Zachary Wu is trapped between his old life and his new one as Shaman's partner. Is anyone right in this fight?

Chapter 16

Brad is asked to make a tough decision by a friend of his dad.
name: Chapter 16

description:
Now + Then

Mister Solenoid battles a new threat in Florida. Then, we visit the past and get a glimpse of the shape of things to come. Featuring artwork by James Ritchey III (GREEN LAMA, TOTAL ECLIPSE) and Armand Villavert (GLADSTONE'S SCHOOL FOR WORLD CONQUERORS, MUPPET ROBIN HOOD).
name: Chapter 5: Now + Then

description:
Virgin's Blood Pt.2

The Crimson Mask has been unmasked!

Virgin races to LeSaint to save its citizens while Hania recounts a story that reveals a huge chunk of his and Virgin's past and how the Father of all Wolfen was born.
name: Virgin's Blood Pt.2

description: Introduction of The Brothers that lay the foundation for what will be the power struggle for survival...or conquest

Dream of Flying

Ariana, a comic book about a teenager's heroic journey for her soul. In a world where dreams speak truth Ariana dreams of flying.
name: Dream of Flying

description:
All Night Long and the End of the Beginning

He Didn't Ask To Be Born.

A sweet girl in a bad situation, a baby found in the desert brush, and an intense, action-packed brawl that pushes the boundaries of good taste and introduces us to a truly unique Superantihero; this is how it all starts in All Night Long and the End of the Beginning.

Baby Badass is a loving homage to the often exploitive comics made famous by some of the 1990's more macho, vengeance-based creations. The broad strokes of blunt, barbaric violence are balanced by a sprawling storyline that gradually opens up to a unexpectedly crazed yet colorful future. The comedic elements are served in a sardonic stew blending natural and geopolitical catastrophe with some of the more extreme elements of a warped, paranoid society. Also, there are some poop jokes.
name: All Night Long and the End of the Beginning

description:
BEYOND the queer sci-fi & fantasy comic anthology features 18 stories by 26 incredible contributors, celebrating unquestionably queer characters hailing from across the spectrum of gender and sexuality, front and centre as the heroes of their own stories.

The softcover edition of the Beyond Anthology is 272 pages of black and white comics from a diverse roster of contributors, with stories starring swashbuckling space pirates, legendary dragon slayers, death-defying astronauts, monster queen royalty, and more!

volume.name: Beyond: The Queer Sci-fi & Fantasy Comic Anthology

description:
A twist on classic haunted horror genre, Blue Moon is a slow-burn, intense graphic novel by Ben Gilboa.

---

Growing up is never easy, because it's about making choices. Who you want to be, what to leave behind.

But for Tim it's an impossible choice.

Because of her. His best friend. The only one who really knows, truly understands him.

The one only he sees and hears.

He can't let go of her. And she won't let him.

Cangaceiros were "social bandits" in some regions of Brazil in the late 19th and early 20th century. They were nomads roaming the region in search of what they considered justice. They fought against land owners and government soldiers. To some people they were heroes, to others were bandits. Officially, the cangaceiros are extinct. But… they are not extinct, damn it! There still is the funny Carrapicho, the last of the cangaceiros!
name: The Cool Cangaceiros

description: In the near future, an already unstable world alliance is set into turmoil when a trio of American teens (David, Carrie, & Dean) are arrested in a foreign country and forced to participate in a highly-televised and brutally twisted version of the Olympic Games called The Deathsport Games. A cadre of sadistic Sportsmen stand between the three youths and their freedom, but losing the games means losing their lives. It's post-apocalyptic sports adventure at it's finest with high speed action sequences written by Ain't It Cool News' Mark L. Miller and gritty art by newcomer Roy Stewart!

Introducing: Evil Jesus!

Evil Jesus is like Jesus, but evil. Enjoy!

Jacob Moore is an unusual teenager, who after the death of his father, begins an early career as a paranormal investigator.

Plagued by dark visions of things to come, he'll meet the girl of his dreams, only to find that the world is much scarier than he ever thought it could be.

This story centers on Wiz (a charming and eccentric gentleman), Hela (a tech enthusiast with hoarding problems), Heyden (a strange kid with even stranger powers) and Adamant (a hot-headed man in power armor who is probably from planet earth) who travel through the planes with the impossible goal of drawing a map of the infinite multiverse.

This six book series will show only some of their adventures along the years: They get hunted like wild animals, help an ancient robot civilization meet their creators, stop an ignoble war and access Gods-only places, all while taking measurements and gathering data. They even manage to get their humongous map back when it gets stolen by the very people they were helping, which leads to the map's ultimate destruction and Wiz seeing the full gargantuan thing at once for the first time.

The comic reports the histories that happen daily to Guillermo Black Flag nicknamed as the Pirate. The book is narrating, by means of emblems, every situation that happens to him. Seemingly situations exist in the Pirate's life that seem that they do not mean anything, but all of them teach the child to face new challenges. Pirate is a boy who lives in his mother´s house, because his parents separated when he was very small.
name: Hi I'm... Pirate

description: John has lost his swimming pool locker wristband, and a very important meeting is mere minutes away. Will he escape an awful, watery fate? Drawn in 24 hours as part of the Lakes International Comics Festival in October 2015.

A man and a woman wake up into a huge and deep grave filled with hundreds of corpses. They have to escape from there as soon as possible. Those dead bodies are infected. At any time the corpses will rise transformed into starving resurrected. And something even more sinister is happening inside the pit...

An original story of zombies as never seen before.

It looks like a condom.

It feels like a condom.

It fits like a condom.

But it's no ordinary condom... it's a killer!

Ralf König's comedy horror classic-which has been produced as a feature film and staged as a life-sized puppet show-is once again available in English!

Saddle your dreams before you ride them

The queen and king are unable to have healthy children. They are helped by a visiting techno-mage. Thus, Prince Amatheus gets born, into a world ridden by a genetic sickness that prevents most people from having normal children. Amatheus is raised by a monitor robot, stuck on story mode. They start their grand adventure: they search the cure for the disease, which is supposedly found on an enchanted palace, guarded by mutants...

In the near future, each human possesses the Nightingale Protocol, an artificial intelligence application that activates when the host is ill. Materializing in an instant, these personal physicians will work tirelessly to cure the patient. But, as one doctor, struggling to adapt to his programming, comes to realize, there may be limits to what this technology can fix.... A.I. meets E.R. in this, another captivating graphic novel in the "Out There" series.

It is Manuel's last day at school. He is happy, because at the end of it, he will be leaving Sydney to meet up with his family. Some weeks ago his father went to work in Darwin as a crocodile keeper in the Kakadu National Park, and his mum and his little sister went with him. Manuel and his family come from the Tumbes river basin in Peru, a place where there are also crocodiles. The fact that his father was familiar with these reptiles was instrumental in winning him the job in the first place.

A poetic take on the Scottish childhood of writer Sean Michael Wilson, in comic book form, drawn by artist Hanna Stromberg. The book mixes together 14 intimate and interesting childhood stories and adventures, with a touch of magical realism.

volume.name: Once Upon A Time In Morningside

description: Back in 2005, a college student from New Orleans wrote a song about the destruction of his hometown. This is the story of that song.

Rebirth

The greatest warrior of history Achilles wakes in a new strange world after his death in Troy with no memories of his life except his name and how he died as well as a driving motivation to become a Legend in this new world!
name: Rebirth

description: It all beings here! The first issue of an anthology featuring comic book content from Red King Press. In this issue Armored Champion, Sniper, Team Chicago, Apples of Idunn, and Steel Soldiers.

The first two chapters of the webcomic "Space Case", following the adventures of a young accountant who applies for an exciting new job in outer space only to discover that there's nothing so familiar as the alien. This PDF contains 56 pages of content, including a behind-the-scenes bonus section and revisions to some pages VS their original online debuts.
name: Brave New Workplace

description: In this introductory issue, two friends are forced to face off in a battle where only one will survive. Meanwhile, other sinister forces are at work and an unknown being's worst fears are confirmed.

Robert Kirby has teamed up with Northwest Press for a digital edition of his comics anthology THREE. This terrific book offers three stories from three different creative teams each issue, and features the cream of the crop of queer comics talents. The first issue includes stories from Eric Orner (The Mostly Unfabulous Social Life of Ethan Green), Joey Alison Sayers (Thingpart, Just So You Know) and Robert Kirby (Boy Trouble, Curbside).

Nine year old Ella has a secret. She's afraid of the dark... or rather the things that live in the dark, in the twisted corners of her nightmares. Ella share her sleepless nights with her stuffed mouse, Winchell, but even he can't keep the monsters at bay for long...
